<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">year</TIMEX> be identified in an annual report to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">parliament</ENAMEX>. (Contributions to
individual <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">candidates</ENAMEX> are unregulated.) The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CDU</ENAMEX> committed a civil <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">offense</ENAMEX> by
ignoring this law, and now faces punitive fines totaling twice the undisclosed
contributions, in addition to having to forfeit the actual contributions to
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">parliament</ENAMEX>. (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Fines</ENAMEX> are deducted from the campaign subsidies the government
gives to the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">party</ENAMEX>.) 

